  XBW15CP.DOS

The command processor of this BW-DOS
version does not include any built-in
basic commands. CP stands for command
processor only.

Its advantage is the low MEMLO ($1D50)
which leaves more free memory for user
programs.

The disadvantage is that no commands
are integrated. All required commands
must be present on disk, ideally in a
directory that is part of the search
path, typically the DOS directory on
the DOS drive. See the DOSDRIVE
command.
